This paper deals with universal source coding, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT). The paper also discusses the Type Size code, which is a code construction technique that falls under the category of coding theory (cs.CC). The paper also involves the analysis of asymptotics, which is a common theme in machine learning (cs.LG) and data structures (cs.DS). Finally, the paper deals with the compression of parametric sources, which could fall under the sub-category of statistical learning (cs.SI).
